race.comment: Tough race to finish. PLATINUM DESTROYER (5) missed the placings two starts back then ran a better race and finished 2.5 lengths away in fourth last time out over 2010m at Kilmore in similar company. Drawn to get back but looks well placed in a very winnable affair. HARSH (8) gave a sight at Tatura last time over 1980m as favourite, beaten narrowly into second. Can improve again and profiles well for this. COASTAL WHISPERS (9) proved too strong two runs ago at Warrnambool, struggling last time in this grade. Wouldn't shock if she bounced back. LOVE SPARKLES (10) hasn't been able to break through for an extended period, the latest effort a seventh over 1765m at Geelong. This looks easier and the trip should suit.
